.TH "CIRCLECI-MIGRATE" "1" "Jun 2026" "circleci-migrate" "CircleCI Org Migration CLI"

.SH NAME
circleci-migrate-terraform - Generate Terraform configurations from an exported manifest.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcircleci-migrate terraform [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
terraform generates Terraform HCL and tfvars files from a circleci-migrate
manifest, targeting the official CircleCI Terraform provider
(CircleCI-Public/circleci, v0.3.x).

.PP
Terraform manages the declarative resources (contexts, context env-vars,
projects, project env-vars); the CLI remains the orchestrator for everything
Terraform cannot do: secrets capture, CIAM, org settings, schedules, checkout
keys, and SSH keys. The generated GAPS.md lists every remaining step with the
exact circleci-migrate command to complete it.

.PP
circleci-migrate terraform generate \\
    --manifest manifest.json \\
    [--secrets bundle.json | --placeholders] \\
    [--mapping mapping.json] \\
    --dest-org-id  \\
    --out ./terraform/


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for terraform


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug logging

.PP
\fB--dest-token\fP=""
	API token for the destination org (env: CIRCLECI_DEST_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--host\fP="https://circleci.com"
	CircleCI host URL (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_HOST, CIRCLECI_HOST, or CIRCLE_URL)

.PP
\fB--source-token\fP=""
	API token for the source org (env: CIRCLECI_SOURCE_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	Personal API token — fallback for both orgs (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_TOKEN or CIRCLE_TOKEN)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcircleci-migrate(1)\fP, \fBcircleci-migrate-terraform-generate(1)\fP
